{"id":"1912.00983","submitter":"Nicholas LaRacuente","authors":"Nicholas LaRacuente","title":"Quasi-factorization and Multiplicative Comparison of Subalgebra-Relative\n  Entropy","comments":"55 pages, 2 figures; corrections and clarifications","journal-ref":"J. Math. Phys. 63, 122203 (2022)","doi":"10.1063/5.0053698","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph cs.IT math.IT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Purely multiplicative comparisons of quantum relative entropy are desirable\nbut challenging to prove. We show such comparisons for relative entropies\nbetween comparable densities, including the relative entropy of a density with\nrespect to its subalgebraic restriction. These inequalities are asymptotically\ntight in approaching known, tight inequalities as perturbation size approaches\nzero. Based on these results, we obtain a kind of inequality known as\nquasi-factorization or approximate tensorization of relative entropy.\nQuasi-factorization lower bounds the sum of a density's relative entropies to\nseveral subalgebraic restrictions in terms of its relative entropy to their\nintersection's subalgebraic restriction. As applications, quasi-factorization\nimplies uncertainty-like relations, and with an iteration trick, it yields\ndecay estimates of optimal asymptotic order on mixing processes described by\nfinite, connected, undirected graphs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Dec 2019 18:23:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 21 Sep 2020 16:12:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 9 Mar 2021 18:56:36 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 19 Apr 2021 06:50:47 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 31 Aug 2021 20:07:08 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Sat, 18 Jun 2022 05:27:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-16"}
