eir morphological features and stratigraphic\ninformation. The age of 79243 craters larger than 3 km in diameter is\nestimated. These identified and aged craters throughout the mid and\nlow-latitude regions of the Moon are crucial for reconstructing the dynamic\nevolution process of the Solar System.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Dec 2019 08:32:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-29"}
